<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">
<html>
<head>
<title>ForgMabber Bookmarklet!</title>
<style type="text/css">
#formgrabberlink {
	background-color:#EFEFEF;
	border:1px solid black;
	color:#1A1A1A;
	padding:4px;
	text-decoration:none;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h2>FormGrabber Bookmarklet!</h2>
<p>Instructions:</p>
<ol>
	<li>Edit this file and replace '&lt;path_to_formgrabber.js&gt;' with the absolute path to where you are hosting formgrabber.js.</li>
	<li>Reload the file and drag the link below to your bookmark toolbar (creating a normal bookmark appears to have issues -- you probably don't want to create a normal bookmark.')</li>
	<li>Any time you want the formgrabber to appear, click the bookmark in your toolbar!</li>
	<li>...</li>
	<li>Profit!</li>
</ol>
<p>
	<a id="formgrabberlink" href="
	javascript:(function(){
	var script=document.createElement('script');
	script.type='text/javascript';
	script.src='http://<path_to_formgrabber.js>/formgrabber.js';
	document.body.appendChild(script);
	})();">FormGrabber</a> &larr; Drag that to the Bookmark Toolbar
</p>
<p>
	As a <strong>quick test</strong>, you can click the link. If the Formgrabber appears, it should work in the browser you're currently using.
</p>
</body>
</html>
